 <text>
  <body>
   <p>Louisville <date when="1861-05-31">May 31/61</date>
<lb/>Geo. W. Johnson, Esq;
<lb/><hi rend="underline">Georgetown</hi>
<lb/>Sir:</p>
<p>At the request of Mrs Rice C Ballard, I have acknowledged the receipt of yours of the <date when="1861-05-28">28<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> inst</date> to her.</p>
<p>Mrs Ballard feels unauthorized to interfere in the matter to which you allude and, believing Judge Boyd will do all that is proper in the case, she begs to refer you to him.</p>
<p>Resf'y
<lb/><hi rend="underline">W. F. Bullock, Jr.</hi><pb/></p>
<p>W. F. Bullock Jr.
<lb/><date when="1861-05-31">May 31. 1861</date>
<lb/></p>
